Name: Mac Address
Description: A media access control address (MAC address) of a computer is a unique identifier assigned to network interfaces for communications.
Definition: <?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="yes"?><DataClasses xmlns="http://www.ibm.com/infosphere/ia/classification/DataclassesDefinition"><DataClass id="MAC" name="Mac Address" example="12:34:56:78:9F" description="A media access control address (MAC address) of a computer is a unique identifier assigned to network interfaces for communications." active="true" provider="IBM"><RegexClassifier><RegularExpression applicableFor="structured_data_only">^(?:[0-9A-Fa-f]{2}([:-]))(?:[0-9A-Fa-f]{2}\1){4}[0-9A-Fa-f]{2}$|(?:^([0-9A-Fa-f]{4}\.){2}[0-9A-Fa-f]{4}$)</RegularExpression></RegexClassifier><DataLengthFilter minLength="14" maxLength="17"/></DataClass></DataClasses>

Name: US Phone Number
Description: US Phone Number is a string of specific numbers that a telephone or cell phone user can dial to reach another telephone or mobile phone in the United States (US).
Definition: <?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="yes"?><DataClasses xmlns="http://www.ibm.com/infosphere/ia/classification/DataclassesDefinition"><DataClass id="USPHN" name="US Phone Number" example="1 (234) 567-8901" description="US Phone Number is a string of specific numbers that a telephone or cell phone user can dial to reach another telephone or mobile phone in the United States (US)." active="true" provider="IBM"><RegexClassifier><RegularExpression applicableFor="structured_data_only">^(\+?1\s*[-\/\.]?)?(\((\d{3})\)|(\d{3}))\s*[-\/\.]?\s*(\d{3})\s*[-\/\.]?\s*(\d{4})\s*(([xX]|[eE][xX][tT])\.?\s*(\d+))*$</RegularExpression></RegexClassifier><DataTypeFilter><LogicalDataType>string</LogicalDataType></DataTypeFilter><DataLengthFilter minLength="9" maxLength="16"/></DataClass></DataClasses>

Name: US Social Security Number
Description: In the United States, a Social Security number (SSN) is a unique nine-digit number issued to U.S. citizens, permanent residents, and temporary (working) residents.
Definition: <?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="yes"?><DataClasses xmlns="http://www.ibm.com/infosphere/ia/classification/DataclassesDefinition"><DataClass id="SSN" name="US Social Security Number" example="123-45-6789" description="In the United States, a Social Security number (SSN) is a unique nine-digit number issued to U.S. citizens, permanent residents, and temporary (working) residents." active="true" provider="IBM"><RegexClassifier><RegularExpression applicableFor="structured_data_only">^([1-578]\d{2}|0[1-9]\d|00[1-9]|6[0-57-9]\d|66[0-57-9])([ \-\.]?)([1-9]\d|0[1-9])\2([1-9]\d{3}|0[1-9]\d{2}|00[1-9]\d|000[1-9])$</RegularExpression></RegexClassifier><DataTypeFilter><LogicalDataType>numeric</LogicalDataType></DataTypeFilter><DataTypeFilter><LogicalDataType>string</LogicalDataType></DataTypeFilter><DataLengthFilter minLength="9" maxLength="11"/></DataClass></DataClasses>

Name: Internet Protocol Address

Name: Iowa State Driver's License
Description: A string representing a driver license of US state Iowa.
Definition: <?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="yes"?><DataClasses xmlns="http://www.ibm.com/infosphere/ia/classification/DataclassesDefinition"><DataClass id="IADL" name="Iowa State Driver's License" example="123XX4567" description="A string representing a driver license of US state Iowa." active="true" provider="IBM"><RegexClassifier><RegularExpression applicableFor="structured_data_only">^([0-6]\d{2}|7[0-6]\d|77[0-2])([ \-\.]?)(\d{2})\2(\d{4})$|^[0-9]{3}[a-zA-Z]{2}[0-9]{4}$</RegularExpression></RegexClassifier><DataTypeFilter><LogicalDataType>string</LogicalDataType></DataTypeFilter><DataLengthFilter minLength="9" maxLength="11"/></DataClass></DataClasses>

Name: IBAN
Description: A string representing an International Bank Account Number.
Definition: <?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="yes"?><DataClasses xmlns="http://www.ibm.com/infosphere/ia/classification/DataclassesDefinition"><DataClass id="IBAN" name="IBAN" example="GB87 BARC 2065 8244 9716 55" description="A string representing an International Bank Account Number." active="true" provider="IBM"><JavaClassifier scope="value" className="com.ibm.infosphere.classification.impl.IBANClassifier"/><DataTypeFilter><LogicalDataType>string</LogicalDataType></DataTypeFilter><DataLengthFilter minLength="14" maxLength="42"/></DataClass></DataClasses>

Name: Kansas State Driver's License
Description: A string representing a driver license of US state Kansas.
Definition: <?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="yes"?><DataClasses xmlns="http://www.ibm.com/infosphere/ia/classification/DataclassesDefinition"><DataClass id="KSDL" name="Kansas State Driver's License" example="K94-12-3456" description="A string representing a driver license of US state Kansas." active="true" provider="IBM"><RegexClassifier><RegularExpression applicableFor="structured_data_only">^([0-6]\d{2}|7[0-6]\d|77[0-2])([ \-\.]?)(\d{2})\2(\d{4})$|^[kK]{1}[0-9]{2}\-[0-9]{2}\-[0-9]{4}$|^[kK]{1}[0-9]{8}$</RegularExpression></RegexClassifier><DataTypeFilter><LogicalDataType>string</LogicalDataType></DataTypeFilter><DataLengthFilter minLength="9" maxLength="11"/></DataClass></DataClasses>

Name: Canada Province Name
Description: Specifies the name of Canada Provinces and territories.
Definition: <?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="yes"?><DataClasses xmlns="http://www.ibm.com/infosphere/ia/classification/DataclassesDefinition"><DataClass id="CAPN" name="Canada Province Name" example="Quebec" description="Specifies the name of Canada Provinces and territories." priority="12" active="true" provider="IBM"><ValueListClassifier caseSensitive="false" allowSubstringMatch="false" squeezeConsecutiveWhiteSpaces="false" valueList="reference/CAProvinceNames.cls"/><DataTypeFilter><LogicalDataType>string</LogicalDataType></DataTypeFilter><DataLengthFilter minLength="2" maxLength="25"/></DataClass></DataClasses>

Name: Canada Post Code
Description: A system of postal codes that are used by Canada Post.
Definition: <?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="yes"?><DataClasses xmlns="http://www.ibm.com/infosphere/ia/classification/DataclassesDefinition"><DataClass id="CAPostCode" name="Canada Post Code" example="H3A 0B1" description="A system of postal codes that are used by Canada Post." active="true" provider="IBM"><RegexClassifier><RegularExpression applicableFor="structured_data_only">^[A-Z]\d[A-Z][ \-]?\d[A-Z]\d$</RegularExpression></RegexClassifier><DataTypeFilter><LogicalDataType>string</LogicalDataType></DataTypeFilter><DataLengthFilter minLength="6" maxLength="7"/></DataClass></DataClasses>

Name: Missouri State Driver's License
Description: A string representing driver license of US state Missouri.
Definition: <?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="yes"?><DataClasses xmlns="http://www.ibm.com/infosphere/ia/classification/DataclassesDefinition"><DataClass id="MODL" name="Missouri State Driver's License" example="012345678" description="A string representing driver license of US state Missouri." active="true" provider="IBM"><RegexClassifier><RegularExpression applicableFor="structured_data_only">^\d{9}$|^[a-zA-Z]{1}[0-9]{5,9}$</RegularExpression></RegexClassifier><DataTypeFilter><LogicalDataType>string</LogicalDataType></DataTypeFilter><DataLengthFilter minLength="6" maxLength="10"/></DataClass></DataClasses>

Name: Political Party
Description: A string representing a Political Party.
Definition: <?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="yes"?><DataClasses xmlns="http://www.ibm.com/infosphere/ia/classification/DataclassesDefinition"><DataClass id="POLITICALPARTY" name="Political Party" example="PDP" description="A string representing a Political Party." active="true" provider="IBM"><ValueListClassifier caseSensitive="false" allowSubstringMatch="false" squeezeConsecutiveWhiteSpaces="false" valueList="reference/PoliticalParties.cls"/><DataTypeFilter><LogicalDataType>string</LogicalDataType></DataTypeFilter><DataLengthFilter minLength="2" maxLength="99"/><ColumnNameFilter><ColumnNameRegularExpression>politic</ColumnNameRegularExpression></ColumnNameFilter></DataClass></DataClasses>

Name: Address  Line 3
Description: Address Line 3 of a multi-line address.
Definition: <?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="yes"?><DataClasses xmlns="http://www.ibm.com/infosphere/ia/classification/DataclassesDefinition"><DataClass id="AddressLine3" name="Address  Line 3" description="Address Line 3 of a multi-line address." priority="12" active="true" provider="IBM"><JavaClassifier scope="column" className="com.ibm.infosphere.classification.impl.AddressLineClassifier"/><DataTypeFilter><LogicalDataType>string</LogicalDataType></DataTypeFilter><DataLengthFilter minLength="4" maxLength="100"/><ColumnNameFilter><ColumnNameRegularExpression>addr.{0,15}(3|three)$</ColumnNameRegularExpression></ColumnNameFilter></DataClass></DataClasses>

Name: Arizona State Driver's License
Description: A string representing driver license of US state Arizona.
Definition: <?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="yes"?><DataClasses xmlns="http://www.ibm.com/infosphere/ia/classification/DataclassesDefinition"><DataClass id="AZDL" name="Arizona State Driver's License" example="A12345678" description="A string representing driver license of US state Arizona." active="true" provider="IBM"><RegexClassifier><RegularExpression applicableFor="structured_data_only">^([0-6]\d{2}|7[0-6]\d|77[0-2])([ \-\.]?)(\d{2})\2(\d{4})$|^[abdyABDY]\d{8}$</RegularExpression></RegexClassifier><DataTypeFilter><LogicalDataType>string</LogicalDataType></DataTypeFilter><DataLengthFilter minLength="9" maxLength="11"/></DataClass></DataClasses>

Name: Account Number
Description: A value representing an Account Number.
Definition: <?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="yes"?><DataClasses xmlns="http://www.ibm.com/infosphere/ia/classification/DataclassesDefinition"><DataClass id="ACCNUM" name="Account Number" example="123456" description="A value representing an Account Number." active="true" provider="IBM"><RegexClassifier><RegularExpression applicableFor="structured_data_only">.</RegularExpression></RegexClassifier><ColumnNameFilter><ColumnNameRegularExpression>^acc(ount)?([ _\-])?(num(ber)?|id|no(\.)?){1}$</ColumnNameRegularExpression></ColumnNameFilter></DataClass></DataClasses>

Name: Louisiana State Driver's License
Description: A string representing a driver license of US state Louisiana.
Definition: <?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="yes"?><DataClasses xmlns="http://www.ibm.com/infosphere/ia/classification/DataclassesDefinition"><DataClass id="LADL" name="Louisiana State Driver's License" example="003456789" description="A string representing a driver license of US state Louisiana." active="true" provider="IBM"><RegexClassifier><RegularExpression applicableFor="structured_data_only">^00[0-9]{7}$</RegularExpression></RegexClassifier><DataTypeFilter><LogicalDataType>string</LogicalDataType></DataTypeFilter><DataLengthFilter minLength="9" maxLength="9"/></DataClass></DataClasses>

Name: Nova Scotia Province Driver's License
Description: A string representing driver license of Canadian province Nova Scotia.
Definition: <?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="yes"?><DataClasses xmlns="http://www.ibm.com/infosphere/ia/classification/DataclassesDefinition"><DataClass id="NSDL" name="Nova Scotia Province Driver's License" example="ABCDE123456789" description="A string representing driver license of Canadian province Nova Scotia." active="true" provider="IBM"><RegexClassifier><RegularExpression applicableFor="structured_data_only">^[a-zA-Z]{5}\d{9}$</RegularExpression></RegexClassifier><DataTypeFilter><LogicalDataType>string</LogicalDataType></DataTypeFilter><DataLengthFilter minLength="14" maxLength="14"/></DataClass></DataClasses>

Name: Relationship
Description: A String representing a relationship between two or more people.
Definition: <?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="yes"?><DataClasses xmlns="http://www.ibm.com/infosphere/ia/classification/DataclassesDefinition"><DataClass id="RELATIONSHIP" name="Relationship" example="Friendship" description="A String representing a relationship between two or more people." active="true" provider="IBM"><ValueListClassifier caseSensitive="false" allowSubstringMatch="false" squeezeConsecutiveWhiteSpaces="false" valueList="reference/Relationship.cls"/><DataTypeFilter><LogicalDataType>string</LogicalDataType></DataTypeFilter><DataLengthFilter minLength="3" maxLength="26"/></DataClass></DataClasses>
